marcus licinius crassus ( ; latin : m·licinivs·p·f·p·n·crassvs;in english : " marcus licinius crassus , son of publius , grandson of publius " c. 115 bc – 53 bc ) was a roman general and politician who played a key role in the transformation of the roman republic into the roman empire .

